This paper discusses the use of maximum entropy inference in uncertain reasoning, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses information theory (cs.IT) and probability theory (cs.DS), which are relevant subfields. Additionally, the paper discusses the comparison of maximum entropy inference with other currently popular methods, which could fall under the subfield of social and information networks (cs.SI).
